52
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:56,570
But we're selling two options and buying two

53
00:01:56,570 --> 00:01:56,990
options.

54
00:01:57,510 --> 00:01:58,650
So how does this work?

55
00:01:58,870 --> 00:01:59,810
Well let me show you.

56
00:02:00,330 --> 00:02:03,690
Stock XYZ is trading at $75 per share.

57
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:07,110
Let's sell the 85 call for $2, and

58
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:09,229
we're also going to sell the 65 put

59
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:09,710
