63
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:19,430
But again, since naked options theoretically have unlimited

64
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:21,450
risk, we are going to buy some protection.

65
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:24,170
So we're also going to buy the 90

66
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:26,890
call for $1, and the 60 put for

67
00:02:26,890 --> 00:02:27,330
$1.

68
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:29,710
And I know that keeping track with all

69
00:02:29,710 --> 00:02:31,910
